cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as object detection and orientation estimation using CNN-based regression and classification methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new approach that takes into account the Riemannian structure of the orientation space, which suggests a possible fit with the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper deals with robotics-related tasks such as object manipulation, which could place it in the cs.RO (Robotics) category. The paper also proposes a data augmentation strategy, which could suggest a fit with the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper deals with 3D object orientation estimation, which could suggest a fit with the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
